          <title>
            <string language="en">How glucose in transported to the cells</string>
            <string language="x-mt-de">Wie Glukose innen transportiert zu den Zellen</string>
            <string language="x-mt-fr">Comment glucose dedans transporté aux cellules</string>

            <string language="x-mt-it">Come glucosio dentro trasportato alle cellule</string>

          </title>
          <description>
            <string language="en">This diagram shows that enzymes in the small intestine breaks down starch into glucose and are transported into the body cells by means of the blood vessels.</string>
          </description>

          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-de">Dieses Diagramm zeigt, daß Enzyme im kleinen 
Darm hinunter Stärke in Glukose bricht und wird in die Körperzellen 
mittels der $blutgefässe transportiert.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-fr">Ce diagramme prouve que les enzymes dans le petit
intestin décompose l'amidon en glucose et est transporté dans les 
cellules de corps à l'aide des vaisseaux sanguins.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-pt">Este diagrama mostra que os enzymes no intestine 
pequeno quebram abaixo o starch no glucose e é transportado nas 
pilhas de corpo por meio das embarcações de sangue.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-it">Questo schema indica che gli enzimi nel piccolo 
intestino analizza l'amido in glucosio ed è trasportato nei 
somatociti per mezzo dei vasi sanguigni.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-el">Αυτό το διάγραμμα δείχνει ότι τα ένζυμα στο λεπτό 
έντερο χωρίζουν το άμυλο σε γλυκόζη και μεταφέρεται στα κύτταρα 
σωμάτων με τη βοήθεια των σκαφών αίματος.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-es">Este diagrama muestra que las enzimas en el 
intestino pequeño analizan el almidón en la glucosa y se transporta 
en las células de cuerpo por medio de los vasos sanguíneos.</string>
          </description>
